{
  "stem": "12904.3",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And as long-- I was, you know, in marriage and divorce and widowed and back to graduate school.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I really didn't have the money or the time, you know, to do it, and I had to work for a living.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And my parents were then sick and I couldn't-- didn't feel I could leave St.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Louis.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I was staying here.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I was not sure-- not that sure that I wanted to.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then I decided.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I had some letters from my relatives who are still there, and from some friends of my father's in a different city-- Darmstadt-- inviting me to come back and to stay with them.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I decided I would do it, and I went by myself then at that time.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And as I said, it was not all pleasant and the memories were not pleasant.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that's why I then decided in '89, when I was invited again, that I would try to make it have a more pleasant experience and then find closure and live that rather than the bad experience in-- well, I had been back. '69 I went with a girlfriend from here who had never been abroad, never been in Europe.",
      "word_count": 60
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And she went with me and we had an experience then in-- in a place by [NON-ENGLISH], where my mother's youngest brother, the one who had been in camp and he and his wife were then in a retirement place in Bavaria.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And when-- one evening, when we were going to go back to our hotel, my friend and I, we had lost our way.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We couldn't remember exactly how to get back.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I stopped.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I said, I can ask.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I know German, after all.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
